Ask HN: VM hosting that could start under a second?
text:
I have a use case that requires starting a VM (or Docker image, though less ideal) in under a few seconds, using a pre-setup image.

I need to run them for 1-2 minutes and then kill them, i.e. looking for a hosting provider that charges in small increments (seconds or minutes).

What are my options?

title: Ask HN: What is the new term for 'slashdotted'?
text: Slashdotted itself might be 20 years old, and the wiki page suggests that farked and drudged have made appearances, but is there anything more generic? A different, better way of saying, 'my site is getting a monumental amount of traffic because i tweeted something that went viral'?
